                <h2>Listing Process</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="right">
                <p>At Go Investment, we understand that getting listed can be a crucial step for businesses looking to raise capital and expand their operations. That is why we have developed a streamlined process for businesses to get listed on our platform. <br></p>

                <ul>
                    <li><span class="list-header">Initial screening:</span> We review the business's financials, operations, and management team to ensure that it meets our listing criteria.</li>
                    <li><span class="list-header">Due diligence:</span> We conduct a thorough due diligence process to ensure that the business is a good fit for our platform and that it has the potential for strong returns on investment.</li>
                    <li><span class="list-header">Business plan review:</span> We review the business plan to ensure that it aligns with our investment philosophy and that the proposed use of funds is clear and realistic.</li>
                    <li><span class="list-header">Listing presentation:</span> We work with the business to create a listing presentation that highlights the key aspects of the business and its growth potential.</li>
                    <li><span class="list-header">Approval and listing:</span> After completing the above steps, we present the business to our investment committee for approval. Once approved, the business will be listed on our platform and made available to our investors.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    Our IPO (Initial Public Offering) allows companies to raise capital by listing their historical sales to the public. By going public, a company can gain access to a larger pool of potential investors and increase its visibility and credibility. However, the process of going public can be complex and time-consuming, and it may also subject the company to increased regulatory scrutiny and financial reporting requirements. Go Investment helps companies navigate the IPO process by providing services such as financial and legal advice, underwriting, and marketing.
                    We understand that getting listed can be a complex process, which is why we work closely with businesses to guide them through the process and ensure that they are well-prepared for listing.
                </p>

            </div>
