        <div class="process">
            <div class="left">
                <h2>Being a Listed Company</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="right">
                <p>Well in advance of the first day of investing, the company must have routines in place regarding complaince with rule and regulation that aplly to the listed companies. In the day-to-day operations of the companies, such rules mainly concern the managing of inside information and notification of certain transactions.<br><br>

                    <span class="list-header">Disclosure of Information:</span> As a listed company, the company is obliged to supply the market with relevant, reliable, accurate and timely information pursuant to Go Investment. A listed company must as soon as possible disclose information of a precise nature, relating, directly or indirectly, to GO INVESTMENT<br><br>
                    The disclosure of inside information must take place as soon as possible, i.e, in conjuction ith the adoptation of any resolution, the occurence of any election, or any other circumstance constituting inside information becoming known to the company. In other words, "as soon as possible" implies that the publication may not take longer that the time it takes to compile and publish the information. This indicates that a press release, and all other parts of the communication tool package, should be drafted prior to the decisions being made. The information must be accurate, relevant and reliable; companies must not omit any fatc that may be likely to affect the assessment of such information.
                    <br><br>

                    <span class="list-header">Delayed Disclosure</span>
                    A company may delay the disclosure of inside information. Such a delay presupposes that the immediate disclosure of the inside information is likely to prejudice the legitimate interests of the companyy, that the delay is not llikely to mislead the public and that the company is abe to ensure the confidentiality of the delayed information.

                    The Certified Adviser shall be notified if the company decides to delay the disclosure oof information. The decision to delay disclosure and the date and time of the decision shall be documented in wirting, As long as the issuer is able to justify its decision to delay, the issuer shall not be required to keep a record of that explanation. However, the company will be temporarily inactive ont eh market. As soon as the disclosures gets submitted the company will be active on the market again.

                    <br><br>

                    <span class="list-header">Service Fee:</span>
                    Go Investment applies a 0.50% service fee on every transaction made through the platform. This fee is applicable to both business and investors, ensuring fairness and consistency accros all users. The purpose of the service fee is to support the ongoing development and maintainance of the plartforn, enabling Go Investment to introduce new features, enhance security measures, and provide reliable customer support. by Implementing a transparent fee structure, Go Investment aims to foster a sustainable ecosystem that benefits all parties involved. the sefvice fee is prominently displayed to users before initiating any transaction, allowing them to make informed decisions. Go Investment actively monitors marjet trends and explores cost optimiztion startegies to ansure that the fee remains competitive within the industry. Overall, the service fee demonstrates Go Investment's commitment to delivering high-quality services and facilitating trustwoorthy financial transactions for business and investors.

                </p>
